main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Vandalia, Ohio on April 6, 1965.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2 to 3 minutes and involved a single large light,The witness described no noise associated with the sighting,The object appeared to be moving rapidly from west to northeast,The report concluded insufficient data for a definitive evaluation,The original report was part of Project Blue Book documentation.
sighted object: a large light in the sky
